textBeforeTable: Track Listing This bespectacled blue-eyed soul wunderkind with the wavy blond mop has taken the music world by storm, and he’s only 24 and barely signed. You wouldn’t guess that such a raw, bluesy soul voice would come out of a kid who looks like this, but give him a spin and you’ll be hooked. His newest features Raphael Saadiq’s rhythm section and the Tower of Power horns, and it’s a seriously funky southern-soul workout, dominated by Stone’s striking vocals, which bear comparison to Stevie Wonder, Chris Robinson or Jamie Lidell.
